7 SECTION 12. IC 6-1.1-18.5-13, AS AMENDED BY P.L.68-2025,
8 SECTION 62, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
9 JANUARY 1, 2026 (RETROACTIVE)]: Sec. 13. With respect to an
10 appeal filed under section 12 of this chapter, the department may find
11 that a civil taxing unit should receive any one (1) or more of the
12 following types of the following relief:
13 (1) Permission to the civil taxing unit to increase its levy in excess
14 of the limitations established under section 3 or 25 of this chapter,
15 as applicable, if in the judgment of the department the increase is
16 reasonably necessary due to increased costs of the civil taxing
17 unit resulting from annexation, consolidation, or other
18 extensions of governmental services by the civil taxing unit to
19 additional geographic areas. With respect to annexation,
20 consolidation, or other extensions of governmental services in
21 a calendar year, if those increased costs are incurred by the civil
22 taxing unit in that calendar year and more than one (1)
23 immediately succeeding calendar year, the unit may appeal under
24 section 12 of this chapter for permission to increase its levy under
25 this subdivision based on those increased costs in any of the
26 following:
27 (A) The first calendar year in which those costs are incurred.
28 (B) One (1) or more of the immediately succeeding four (4)
29 calendar years.
30 (2) Permission to the civil taxing unit to increase its levy in
31 excess of the limitations established under section 3 or 25 of
32 this chapter, as applicable, if the department finds that the
33 quotient determined under STEP SIX of the following
34 formula is equal to or greater than one and two-hundredths
35 (1.02):
36 STEP ONE: Determine the three (3) calendar years that
37 most immediately precede the ensuing calendar year.
38 STEP TWO: Compute separately, for each of the calendar
39 years determined in STEP ONE, the quotient (rounded to
40 the nearest ten-thousandth (0.0001)) of the sum of the civil
41 taxing unit's total assessed value of all taxable property
42 divided by the sum determined under this STEP for the
2026 IN 81—LS 6420/DI 120

